This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 9, 2011, as Leif Erikson Day. The proclamation highlights the historical significance of Leif Erikson and his crew, who were the first Europeans to set foot on North America over a millennium ago. It mentions their bravery and determination in sailing into the unknown, founding the settlement of Vinland in modern-day Canada. The proclamation also recognizes the contributions of Nordic-American culture to the United States and encourages the celebration of Nordic-American heritage. The proclamation was authorized by Congress in 1964.